{"id": "2026-07-20-news-us-strikes-iran-for-ninth-consecutive-night-as-t", "date": "2026-07-20", "stream": "news", "headline": "US strikes Iran for ninth consecutive night as third US soldier killed and Hormuz fight escalates", "summary": "The US carried out a ninth night of air strikes on Iran on 20 July amid a collapsing ceasefire and a fight for the Strait of Hormuz; a third US service member was killed, Iran retaliated on Gulf-state bases, and Brent crude rose above $90.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/20/us-bombs-iran-for-ninth-consecutive-night-as-hormuz-tensions-escalate", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "The US struck Iran for a ninth consecutive night early Monday (20 July) as a month-old ceasefire kept unravelling and the fight for the Strait of Hormuz widened. Iranian state media (IRIB, Fars) reported explosions from the Gulf ports of Bandar Mahshahr and Bandar Imam Khomeini to Jask, Sirik, Konarak and Chabahar on the southern coast, and — for the first time in this escalation — as far north as Tabriz. The US military said it hit command centres, air defences, coastal-surveillance and missile/drone launch sites to degrade Iran's ability to attack shipping; Iran's Revolutionary Guard (IRGC) said it fired missiles and drones from Lorestan at US assets, claiming strikes on airbases in Jordan (Aqaba, Azraq) and Kuwait (Ali Al Salem), with sirens also sounding in Bahrain. The US now confirms a third service member killed in recent days in Jordan and Iraq; President Trump said the latest strikes were carried out \"in honour\" of those troops and repeated that \"Iran cannot have a nuclear weapon.\" Washington says it is enforcing a naval blockade of Iranian ports while the IRGC says two oil tankers \"exploded\" overnight attempting what it called an \"unsafe\" corridor through the strait. Secretary of State Marco Rubio, speaking in the Philippines, said the US remained \"open to diplomacy\" but \"it has to be real,\" urging other countries to help protect Hormuz shipping. Brent crude rose above $90 a barrel for the first time in over a month — a direct cost for import-dependent Switzerland.", "why": "A great-power air campaign, mounting US casualties and a contested chokepoint that carries a fifth of the world's seaborne oil is the combination most likely to turn a regional war into a global economic shock.", "thread_id": "2026-06-20-cyber-papers-iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-again-over-israeli", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-20", "event_date": "2026-07-20", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["United States", "Iran", "Strait of Hormuz", "Donald Trump"]}
{"id": "2026-07-20-news-andy-burnham-becomes-uk-prime-minister-replacing", "date": "2026-07-20", "stream": "news", "headline": "Andy Burnham becomes UK prime minister, replacing Keir Starmer", "summary": "Andy Burnham took office as UK prime minister on 20 July after Keir Starmer resigned, pledging a 10-year plan, cost-of-living action and scrapping the digital-ID scheme.", "url": "https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2026/jul/20/andy-burnham-new-prime-minister-pm-keir-starmer-labour-no-10-downing-street-speech-cabinet-uk-politics-latest-news-updates", "source_domain": "theguardian.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["new source"], "topics": ["politics", "world"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "Andy Burnham took office as UK prime minister on Monday (20 July), completing Labour's mid-term handover after Keir Starmer resigned. The 56-year-old mayor of Greater Manchester — a lifelong Labour member with no seat in the current Parliament — was named party leader on 17 July through an internal process in which no rival stood, and received King Charles III's authority to form a government at Buckingham Palace on Monday before entering No 10. He is the UK's fifth prime minister in four years (seventh since 2010). Burnham promised a \"10-year plan,\" \"early moves\" on the cost of living, and a \"reset of priorities\" whose first concrete step is scrapping Starmer's digital-ID scheme; prisons minister James (Lord) Timpson resigned as the reshuffle began. He has signalled a \"change of emphasis\" toward the North Sea oil-and-gas industry — enough for Trump to claim on social media, disputed by Burnham's allies, that Britain would open the basin \"all the way.\"", "why": "Britain gets its seventh leader in a decade amid a rising Reform UK, and Burnham's instincts — devolution, renationalising rail and water, a warmer line on Europe — could reshape UK–EU relations that bear directly on Switzerland's own bilateral track.", "thread_id": "2026-06-22-cyber-papers-keir-starmer-resigns-as-uk-prime-minister-openin", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-22", "event_date": "2026-07-20", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Andy Burnham", "Keir Starmer", "United Kingdom", "Labour Party"]}
{"id": "2026-07-20-news-drc-ebola-outbreak-nears-1-000-deaths-as-canada", "date": "2026-07-20", "stream": "news", "headline": "DRC Ebola outbreak nears 1,000 deaths as Canada imposes entry ban", "summary": "An Ebola outbreak in eastern DR Congo has killed close to 1,000 of 2,344 confirmed cases; Canada barred entry to recent travellers on 20 July, against WHO advice.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/international/ebola-ausbruch-fast-1000-todesopfer-in-kongo-kinshasa", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["health", "world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Ebola outbreak in eastern DR Congo has killed close to 1,000 people out of 2,344 confirmed cases, and Canada barred entry to recent travellers on Monday (20 July). More than one in three confirmed infections has been fatal in what authorities call the fastest-spreading Ebola outbreak on record, which began about two months ago in the country's east; the death toll has jumped from roughly 600 reported on 9 July. Canada's health agency said its ban — blocking non-residents who were in the DRC within the past 21 days — took effect Monday, following a similar US restriction last week. Both go against WHO guidance, which rates the risk of international spread as low and advises against travel or trade restrictions on the grounds they stigmatise affected countries and hamper epidemic control.", "why": "A lethal, fast-moving outbreak colliding with unilateral border closures reopens the hard pandemic-era question of whether such bans protect anyone or mainly punish the countries doing the containing.", "thread_id": "2026-06-22-cyber-papers-ebola-cases-surpass-1-000-in-dr-congo-amid-viole", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-22", "event_date": "2026-07-20", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["DR Congo", "Ebola", "WHO", "Canada"]}
{"id": "2026-07-20-news-aargau-prosecutor-seeks-life-sentence-for-ex-svp", "date": "2026-07-20", "stream": "news", "headline": "Aargau prosecutor seeks life sentence for ex-SVP MP Patrick Frei", "summary": "The Aargau public prosecutor on 20 July demanded life imprisonment for former SVP cantonal MP Patrick Frei, accused of drugging and sexually assaulting several women and a minor and of attempted murder.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/anklage-wegen-versuchten-mords-aargauer-ex-politiker-soll-lebenslang-ins-gefaengnis-darum-geht-s", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Aargau public prosecutor on Monday (20 July) demanded a life sentence for former SVP cantonal MP Patrick Frei, accused of drugging and sexually assaulting several women and a minor. Frei, 57, a former member of the Aargau Grand Council held in pretrial detention, faces charges that include multiple counts of attempted murder, aggravated rape and sexual acts with children; prosecutors allege he rendered victims unconscious with knock-out drops before assaulting them. The case came to light in September 2023 after the mother of one victim caught him in the act.", "why": "A demand for Switzerland's most severe penalty against a former elected official makes this one of the gravest political-figure criminal cases the canton has seen, and the verdict will test how the courts weigh the attempted-murder framing built on the alleged drugging.", "thread_id": "2026-07-20-news-aargau-prosecutor-seeks-life-sentence-for-ex-svp", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-20", "event_date": "2026-07-20", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Patrick Frei", "SVP", "Aargau"]}
{"id": "2026-07-20-news-fire-guts-attic-of-lucerne-hotel-60-evacuated", "date": "2026-07-20", "stream": "news", "headline": "Fire guts attic of Lucerne hotel; 60 evacuated", "summary": "A Sunday-evening fire in the attic of the Hotel Continental Park near Lucerne station forced about 60 evacuations and lightly injured one firefighter.", "url": "https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/2026/article/lucerne-important-incendie-dans-un-hotel-pres-de-la-gare-29307552.html", "source_domain": "rts.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "A fire gutted the attic of the Hotel Continental Park near Lucerne's railway station on Sunday evening (19 July), forcing about 60 evacuations. The alarm was raised at 19:39 and the blaze — which destroyed several attic rooms — was under control by around 22:00, Lucerne city fire services said. One firefighter was lightly injured in the arm and taken to hospital; six other people and two firefighters were checked for possible smoke inhalation, and guests and staff were evacuated in time. Around 120 responders from several fire corps were mobilised, and crews prevented the flames from spreading to neighbouring buildings.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-20-news-fire-guts-attic-of-lucerne-hotel-60-evacuated", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-20", "event_date": "2026-07-19", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Lucerne", "Hotel Continental Park"]}
